        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Organization of Sports Competitions and Training Programs&amp;quot; was launched by the Department of Youth Welfare and prantiy rakshak dal (PRD), Government of Uttarakhand. The scheme aims to promote sports and identify grassroots-level talent among youth through structured competitions and training. \n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - Organizing Khel Mahakumbh Competitions – Various sports competitions are organized for the age groups Under-14, Under-17, and Under-21.\n  - Prizes are awarded for first, second, and third places as follows:\n\n**Sl. No.****Level****1****st** **Rank (Cash Prize ₹)****2****nd** **Rank (Cash Prize ₹)****3****rd** **Rank (Cash Prize ₹)**1Gram Panchayat₹300/-₹200/-₹150/-2Block Development ₹500/-₹400/-₹300/-3District Level₹800/-₹600/-₹400/-4State Level₹1,500/-₹1,000/-₹700/-\n  - During the competitions, talented players who perform best at the Block Development levels and District levels are identified by the department and provided free training prior to state-level participation.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to promote sports & identify grassroots-level talent among youth through structured competitions & training. Players are provided with cash prizes and free training, & participation is encouraged at multiple levels, including Gram Panchayat, Development Block, District, and State.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
